Flanker Josh Strauss had initially signed a two-year deal with the three-time Super Rugby champions. PRETORIA - Flanker Josh Strauss has been released by the Bulls. Strauss had initially signed a two-year deal with the three-time Super Rugby champions. But his short stint has come to an end as the restructuring at Loftus continues. The flanker captained the Lions before relocating to Scotland where he played over a hundred matches for Glasgow Warriors. Strauss went on to play international rugby for the Scots and was capped 15 times. He only played one match for the Bulls.